AB  - To estimate a sample quantile’s variance, the quantile spacing method involves smoothing parameter m. When m,n→∞, the corresponding Studentized test statistic is asymptotically N(0,1). Holding m fixed instead, the asymptotic distribution contains the Edgeworth expansion term capturing the variance of the quantile spacing. Consequently, the fixed-m distribution is more accurate than the standard normal under both asymptotic frameworks. A testing-optimal m is proposed to maximize power subject to size control. In simulations, the new method controls size better than similar methods while maintaining good power. Throughout are results for two-sample quantile treatment effect inference. Code is available online.
